tip.text: If you've ever wondered what the right way to make your own yakiniku - this place is a must visit. The beef cuts are all fantastic, but save room for the pork jowl.
Try the 5 course - especially when Beppe is in the kitchen. Wonderful mix of comfort style food with very sophisticated preparation!

tip.text: Creative dishes without relying on super exotic ingredients. Solid meal from start to finish.
Try the fish tacos, and get the set meal - decent value for the two tacos and a side of rice and beans.
Always enjoyed Chef Malcolm's food - the change to a tasting menu format really allows him to shine on flavored and plating. Must try dessert- the Buah Keluak ice cream.
Soba shop and patisserie are worth trying here. The views are also fantastic
Try the braised pork trotters noodle soup - oishii!

Excellent and warm service + approachable Italian cuisine = going back often. Tues/Sun no corkage fee - sweet!
Must have - cold angel hair pasta. Also if you can get a booking during restaurant week it is a ridiculously good bargain.
Good balance of price and quality. Always happy to dine somewhere the chef/owner is still actively involved after all these years

tip.text: Must tries- xxl pizzas and the deep fried portobello mushroom appetizer.
Set lunch deals are a good deal.
A lot of activities for kids 110cm and under. Rides for older kids are fun for adults. Just plan for long lines.
A bit pricey, but good pizzas and pastas. The clam soup is also quite nice.
Food challenge: order the "VIP" set - bountiful variety of dishes at ginormous serving sizes.
Fun experience if you'd like to try out the local seafood. Make sure you are clear about the cooking prices for the fish - it can triple your per person costs.
Ridiculously large portions. Try ordering a few appetizers and a main to share. Try the avocado rolls - still can't find anything like it.
Fresh cockles and creamy laksa. Worth the trek east if you don't live nearby.
Ana lounge is one of my favorites for the udon/soba cafe and whiskey bar.

tip.text: Steaks and mixed drinks are still good. Service seems to have slipped this past year. No longer as friendly or mindful as before.
Ok so the Nami sausages are pretty tasty. Seriously.
Red bean and shaved ice is good. Can't go wrong with a hand drip coffee either.
